"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-sports-2024-7-17-from-bonmati-to-marta-five-top-footballers-to-watch-at-paris-olympics-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"With women's football one of the most hotly contested sports at Paris 2024, Al Jazeera runs through five names to watch.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 64, \"end\": 74, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.765282019642736e-16, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 76, \"end\": 86, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera_English\", \"score\": 0.9291959092586736, \"rank\": 0.07586324615554292, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera_English\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera_English\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Save  Share  The United States team heads to the Paris 2024 Olympic Games as favourites to claim the women's football gold.\", \"from\": 122, \"to\": 245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 139, \"end\": 152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999998321982, \"rank\": 1.6793938514853774e-10, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is hardly surprising given their four wins in the eight Olympics since the sport was added to the roster of events.\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 367, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"World champions Spain and hosts France are hot on their heels, but it is hard to rule out Brazil, with arguably the greatest female footballer in history.\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 385, \"end\": 390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999984031172988, \"rank\": 1.5968852067501028e-06, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 401, \"end\": 407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.110014823944115e-14, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 459, \"end\": 465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998930361529, \"rank\": 1.0696372805614898e-07, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's football tournament begins on July 25.\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 575, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are our top five players to watch:  Marta Vieira da Silva, simply known as Marta, is arguably the greatest female footballer in history with six FIFA Player of the Year awards to her name.\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 617, \"end\": 638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marta_(footballer)\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marta Vieira da Silva\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marta_(footballer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marta_(footballer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 38-year-old has yet to win a major global trophy, having won silver at the 2004 and 2008 Olympics while also finishing on the losing side in the 2007 World Cup to Germany.\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 938, \"end\": 945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9897580750897957, \"rank\": 0.010347907400871131, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is an oddity that Brazil, who have won eight of the nine Copa Americas since its inauguration in 1991, have failed to transfer their continental dominance onto the world stage.\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 1127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 969, \"end\": 975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998930361529, \"rank\": 1.0696372805614898e-07, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA_Americas\", \"score\": 0.9999999999745341, \"rank\": 2.5221495610989387e-11, \"text\": \"Americas\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA_Americas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA_Americas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, Marta holds the record for the most goals (17) scored at either men's or women's World Cups.\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1229, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The striker, who plays for Orlando Pirates in the US, has announced this will be her last shot at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1266, \"end\": 1273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pittsburgh_Pirates\", \"score\": 0.9999999900387593, \"rank\": 3.4602441209521082e-09, \"text\": \"Pirates\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pittsburgh_Pirates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pittsburgh_Pirates\"}, {\"begin\": 1281, \"end\": 1283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.607296219408455e-21, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kundananji will carry the weight of her nation on her shoulders to the Olympics - and the expectation associated with being the world's most expensive female footballer.\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 24-year-old signed for National Women's Soccer League (NWSL) expansion team Bay FC in February from Spanish club Madrid CFF for a fee of $788,000.\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1574, \"end\": 1578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Women's_Soccer_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.094765321135459e-17, \"text\": \"NWSL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Women's_Soccer_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Women's_Soccer_League\"}, {\"begin\": 1619, \"end\": 1626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9971351533385888, \"rank\": 0.0028704869555084447, \"text\": \"Spanish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}, {\"begin\": 1632, \"end\": 1642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madrid_CFF\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madrid CFF\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madrid_CFF\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madrid_CFF\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The striker, who played for Zambia in last year's Women's World Cup, has 10 goals in 18 internationals.\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999969069779212, \"rank\": 3.055259522196025e-06, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1725, \"end\": 1734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\", \"score\": 0.9999632853123981, \"rank\": 2.601598181373628e-05, \"text\": \"World Cup\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In her time with Madrid, she scored 33 goals in 43 Liga F games having joined from Sociedad Deportiva Eibar in 2022.\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1789, \"end\": 1795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Real_Madrid_CF\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1683282410740964e-24, \"text\": \"Madrid\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Real_Madrid_CF\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Real_Madrid_CF\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonmati was named the2023 Ballon d'Or winnerafter a stellar couple of seasons saw her sweep all before her for club and country.\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 2018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 26-year-old, who received her award at a ceremony alongside men's winner Lionel Messi, helped her side claimthe 2023 World Cup in Australiawith a 1-0 win against England.\", \"from\": 2020, \"to\": 2194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2104, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lionel_Messi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.113477363088853e-69, \"text\": \"Messi\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lionel_Messi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lionel_Messi\"}, {\"begin\": 2186, \"end\": 2193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999992570167737, \"rank\": 7.429837268350312e-07, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The midfielderwon the Golden Ball awardas the tournament's best player.\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2267, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonmati scored six goals in as many games, including netting in the final, for Barcelona as they beat Lyon 2-0 last season to claim the Champions League trophy for the second successive year.\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2347, \"end\": 2356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Barcelona\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.550526870849925e-22, \"text\": \"Barcelona\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Barcelona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Barcelona\"}, {\"begin\": 2404, \"end\": 2420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.952491426004349e-63, \"text\": \"Champions League\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Horan will captain USA, who are by far the most successful team in the short history of women's football at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2461, \"to\": 2582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2472, \"end\": 2483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_John_Studd\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"captain USA\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_John_Studd\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_John_Studd\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The North Americans have won four golds, two silvers and one bronze - failing to achieve a medal finish only at the 2016 Games.\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The versatile 30-year-old forward was part of the team that lost their semifinal match to Canada at Tokyo 2020 but experienced the podium finish with a 4-3 win against Australia in the bronze medal match.\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2803, \"end\": 2809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.197341223757847e-15, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2813, \"end\": 2818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9796617555336985, \"rank\": 0.020760464302991954, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2881, \"end\": 2890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0821970000956575e-18, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It made up in some way for the defeat on penalties, in which Horan scored her spot kick, to Sweden four years previous at the quarterfinal stage.\", \"from\": 2919, \"to\": 3064, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2980, \"end\": 2985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Horan\", \"score\": 0.9999823191054596, \"rank\": 1.7681207114363832e-05, \"text\": \"Horan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Horan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Horan\"}, {\"begin\": 3011, \"end\": 3017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.026955889381451e-16, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having previously scored\\u00a046 goals in 58 games for Paris Saint-Germain, Horan last year returned to France with Lyon following a seven-year stint in the NWSL with Portland Thorns, where she helped her side to the championship in 2017 and named the league's Most Valuable Player the following season.\", \"from\": 3066, \"to\": 3364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3137, \"end\": 3142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Horan\", \"score\": 0.9999823191054596, \"rank\": 1.7681207114363832e-05, \"text\": \"Horan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Horan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_Horan\"}, {\"begin\": 3165, \"end\": 3171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.110014823944115e-14, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_nat